Finite type-C2 boundary diagnostics
Date: 2026-07-22 UTC

Build
-----
$ make -B -j1 search_su2_level_partial_character_cone
g++ -O2 -std=c++20 -Wall -Wextra -Wpedantic -Wconversion \
    -Wshadow -Werror search_su2_level_partial_character_cone.cpp \
    -o search_su2_level_partial_character_cone

1. Exact finite C2 fundamental transform
-----------------------------------------
$ ./search_su2_level_partial_character_cone finite-c2-fundamental 32 100
...
progress level=32 factors=0..100 entries=1155440
SU2_FINITE_C2_FUNDAMENTAL levels=1..32 factors=0..100 \
entries=1155440 result=PASS

This compares every positive-positive entry of the SU(2)_k
fusion-Hankel defect for Q=[1^n] with the corresponding walk count in
the triangular alcove 0 <= s <= r <= k-1.  The equality and
nonnegativity checks are both exact integer checks.

2. Exact affine top-row cancellation
------------------------------------
$ ./search_su2_level_partial_character_cone finite-c2-wall-generator 40 40
...
progress level=40 labels=1..39 coefficients=335790 nonzero=1560
SU2_FINITE_C2_WALL_GENERATOR levels=2..40 maximum_label=40 \
coefficients=335790 nonzero=1560 result=PASS

For every tested k and 1 <= q < k this checks the full finite C2
expansion

  Psi_(k-1,0) [chi_q(x)+chi_q(y)]
    = Psi_(k-1,q) + Psi_(k-1-q,0),

including that the two displayed coefficients are one and every other
coefficient is zero.

3. Character-positive wall-cone obstruction
--------------------------------------------
$ ./search_su2_level_partial_character_cone finite-c2-wall-cone 8 6
progress level=2 words=7 coefficients=21
SU2_FINITE_C2_WALL_CONE result=FAIL level=3 word=[+2,+2] \
weight=(1,1) coefficient=-2
profile (0,0)=1 (1,1)=-2 (2,0)=2 (2,2)=1

This is an expected falsification result: after two plus generators the
entire finite C2 expansion need not remain character-positive, even though
the row projection required by the simple-current boundary remains
nonnegative in the bounded wall search.

