These are expected falsification results.  They prove that an SCBI switch
cannot act independently on a complementary allocation pair, nor preserve
the cardinality shell of the allocation.

5. Standard finite C2 packet-cone obstructions
-----------------------------------------------
$ ./search_su2_level_partial_character_cone finite-c2-wall-packets 8 6
progress level=2 words=7 coefficients=21 negative_coefficients=0 \
prefixes=21 diagonal_prefix_failures=0 minimum_prefix=0 \
two_layer_packets=14 minimum_two_layer_packet=0
diagonal_prefix_failure level=3 word=[+2,+2,+2] degree=2 \
through_second=1 prefix=-4 profile= (2,0)=2 (1,1)=-6 \
full_profile= (0,0)=5 (1,1)=-6 (2,0)=2 (2,2)=5
progress level=3 words=35 coefficients=189 negative_coefficients=5 \
prefixes=189 diagonal_prefix_failures=4 minimum_prefix=-140 \
two_layer_packets=126 minimum_two_layer_packet=0
progress level=4 words=119 coefficients=1029 negative_coefficients=57 \
prefixes=1029 diagonal_prefix_failures=33 minimum_prefix=-140 \
two_layer_packets=630 minimum_two_layer_packet=0
SU2_FINITE_C2_WALL_PACKETS result=FAIL_TWO_LAYER level=5 \
word=[+1,+1,+3,+3,+4,+4] target=(3,3) packet=-2

These are expected falsification results.  Constant-degree inward prefixes
are not always positive, and even the canonical two-layer packets from the
finite C2 row-product decomposition are not an invariant positive cone.
Their b=1 specializations are the desired simple-current row coefficients
and remain nonnegative in all cases reached before the displayed stronger
packet obstruction.

6. Simple-current exterior-minor identity
------------------------------------------
$ ./search_su2_level_partial_character_cone simple-current-exterior 10 7
progress level=2 words=8 boundary_entries=16 interior_entries=24 \
negative_interior_entries=0
negative_interior level=3 word=[+2,+2] state=(2,1) value=-2
...
progress level=10 words=24309 boundary_entries=218789 \
interior_entries=1113397 negative_interior_entries=165463 \
odd_orbit_entries=40101
SU2_SIMPLE_CURRENT_EXTERIOR levels=2..10 maximum_factors=7 words=24309 \
boundary_entries=218789 interior_entries=1113397 \
negative_interior_entries=165463 odd_orbit_entries=40101 result=PASS

For every word and target this independently compares the coefficient from
e_k wedge e_0 to e_a wedge e_0 under the ordered product of additive fusion
compounds with E_Q(a,k), and checks invariance under the J wedge J=-1
simple-current sector.  All boundary coefficients pass, despite the many
negative interior coefficients.  This is bounded evidence for boundary
positivity, not its uniform proof.

At odd levels the same mode folds the J=+1 sector to its nonnegative orbit
matrices A_q and checks the exact signed-transfer factorization

  dGamma(N_q) = A_q tensor I + (-1)^q I tensor A_q

on every boundary target.  The 40,101 reported odd-orbit entries all agree
exactly with the exterior calculation, including the parity-forced zero in
the paired physical target.
